The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: State-run hydro power generator NHPC today made a disappointing debut on the bourses and settled with just 2 per cent gain over its issue price on the Bombay Stock Exchange. The NHPC shares settled at Rs 36.70, just 70 paise or 1.94 per cent above its issue price of Rs 36 on the BSE.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: The government has decided to pay more for the sugar it purchases from millers, but said it was still working on pricing details. The government has informed the development to Delhi High Court.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Tata Teleservices is planning to raise $1 billion to buy 3G spectrum and fund its GSM mobile expansion plans. The firm had earlier earmarked an investment of $2 billion for the national rollout of its GSM network.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Indias exports declined 28.4 per cent to $13.62 billion in July, the tenth straight month to record a fall. Exports slipped in July on low demand in the United States and the EU.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: IL amp;FS has acquired 88.89 lakh shares of Maytas Infra and will continue to hold the shares till the completion of its open offer for the infrastructure firm.                                                                                                                           
